I think this sounds better than it really ends up being.  I can ,without working at it, get to 3500+ hps.  That is if I have Virtue.  With Aego, its down to 3200 or so.  Arcane Rune adds a 1500 point buffer.<br>
<br>
Should I get to 4200 over 3500, that is one swing of a mob in PoV.  Its just not worth it to add so many hp IF you have to get rid of other things.  If you are being hit by unslowed PoV mobs you are dead.  Its just that simple.  Guess what, your tanks are dead as well.  They just get a few more swings, that is why slow is so powerful.  If I can get a slow in on an add, I can tank in PoV.  Just Arcane rune every time it breaks.  Now its more mana efficient to mezz, but it is possible to tank.<br>
<br>
So, look at aggro control...Horrifying Visions works wonders on an MA Warrior.  Pallys and SK need to use their spell for aggro control.  Space your tash and slow out a bit to give people time to build aggro.<br>
<br>
I prioritize my equipment in the following ways +Int (till its maxed), +Mana, +Resists, +HPs, then +anything else.<br>
